Name: DISTANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES FROM START POINT
DISTANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES FROM FINISH POINT
DISTANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES FROM A Q-ROUTE POINT
CAP STATION DISTANCE INDICATOR
Explanation: AN INDICATOR OF THE DISTANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES OF A COMBAT AIR PATROL (CAP) STATION FROM A REFERENCE POINT, USUALLY THE CENTRE OF THE FORCE. THE LETTER 'A' REPRESENTS 50NM, 'B' 100NM AND SO ON. INTERMEDIATE DISTANCES ARE REPRESENTED BY A SINGLE LETTER CODE FOLLOWED BY 'PLUS' OR 'MINUS' AND A NUMBER OF MILES FROM 5 TO 45 IN 5-MILE INCREMENTS.

ENDURANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES AT PLANNING SPEED
Explanation: THE ENDURANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES OF THE LANDING CRAFT AT THE SPECIFIED PLANNING SPEED.

Name: CAP STATION LENGTH IN NAUTICAL MILES
Explanation: THE LENGTH OF THE ORBIT A COMBAT AIR PATROL TASKED UNIT OR A/C SHALL OCCUPY WHILE ON STATION.

Name: GROUP TRANSIT LONGITUDINAL INTERVAL, NAUTICAL MILES
SIGNAL INTERCEPT DISTANCE IN NAUTICAL MILES
Explanation: THE DISTANCE BETWEEN AN OBJECT AND AN INTERCEPTED SIGNAL POSITION MEASURED IN NAUTICAL MILES.
